messages.message: Do we need to manually edit mypy grpc stubs for protos (e.g. mount_service_pb2_grpc.pyi (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/stubs/instabase/protos/mount_service/mount_service_pb2_grpc.pyi))? The file says it is auto generated, but @Xindi Xu's comment here (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C011FHLBN8N/p1738889514062659?thread_ts=1738886105.458299&cid=C011FHLBN8N) seems to suggest we need to manually edit these files (and `make build-protos` doesn't seem to generate it).
cc: @Cheryl Zhou @mfichman last two folks to update this file
theres a .proto file associated with this, im assuming youâ€™ve edited the corresponding one and ran that command in the same directory?

I think I see some inconsistencies in the file, so I don't think it was auto generated in the last commit at least. Going to manually edit it for now to fix CI for my PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72632).

That is:
x_grpc.pyi => manual
x.pyi => auto
Unless @Victor Zeng recently changed something? I think these have always been manually generated
IIRC build_protos.py has never had python GRPC /pyi support  since I've been here. Someone might have run the tool manually though

Got it, thanks for confirming. This file had `# Generated by the gRPC Python protocol compiler plugin. DO NOT EDIT!` at the top, so I was confused. I can look into generating these automatically post my current pr (or at the very least remove the `auto generated` comment).
I remember asking Shaunak the same question back when he was here :slightly_smiling_face:
re: autogen, I'm working on fixing that already as part of the switch off of Bazel
Go is pretty much done, but Python has some work to do (clearly!)
